'''Matt Scott''' (born March 27, 1985) is an American [[wheelchair basketball]] player.

==Biography==
Matt Scott was born in [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]]. He was on the gold medal winning US team at the [[2007 Parapan American Games]] in Brazil and 2011 as well. He also won a silver medal at [[Wheelchair Basketball World Championship|IWBF World Championship]] in 2006 and then won a bronze one at the same place in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.teamusa.org/Athletes/SC/Matt-Scott.aspx|title=Matt Scott|publisher=[[United States Olympic Committee]]|work=Team USA|accessdate=July 17, 2013}}</ref> He was nominated for the [[Best Male Athlete with a Disability ESPY Award]] for this.<ref>[http://www.jsonline.com/sports/statecolleges/29493439.html Milwaukee Journal Sentinel]</ref><ref>[http://www.yankton.net/articles/2008/07/02/sports/doc486afe9a9601e110865917.txt Yankton Press and Dakotan]</ref> He has [[spina bifida]] and competed in the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]] and [[2008 Summer Paralympics]]. He was the first US Paralympian to star in a [[Nike, Inc.]] advertisement. He attended University of Wisconsin-Whitewater. He is playing for GSD Porto Torres Wheelchair Basketball Team right now.{{when|date=August 2016}}<!-- when is "right now"? -->{{citation needed|date=August 2016}}

