'''Paul Kenward''' is a British businessman, who is [[managing director]] of [[British Sugar]]. He is the husband of the British [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]] [[Victoria Atkins]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Paul Kenward |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=242243141&privcapId=5478700 |website=www.bloomberg.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=A message from British Sugar MD, Paul Kenward {{!}} Our MD |url=https://www.britishsugar.co.uk/about-us/our-managing-director |website=British Sugar}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=This is Paul Kenward, husband of Victoria Atkins MP who is the UK drugs minister. He grows cannabis for a living. - CLEAR |url=https://www.clear-uk.org/paul-kenward-husband-victoria-atkins-mp-uk-drugs-minister-grows-cannabis-living/ |work=CLEAR |date=9 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bradshaw |first1=Julia |title=British Sugar to cultivate cannabis plants in Norfolk for GW Pharmaceuticals |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2016/10/25/british-sugar-to-cultivate-cannabis-plants-in-norfolk-for-gw-pha/ |work=The Telegraph |date=25 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Drugs minister accused of 'hypocrisy on a grand scale' over husband's involvement in legal cannabis farm |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/drugs-minister-victoria-atkins-hypocrisy-cannabis-paul-kenward-british-sugar-a8356056.html |work=The Independent}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Gilligan |first1=Andrew |title=Drug minister Victoria Atkins’s husband oversees cannabis farm |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/drug-minister-victoria-atkinss-husband-oversees-cannabis-farm-hv5q25pqr |work=The Sunday Times |date=13 May 2018 |language=en}}</ref>

